Definition: facing or experiencing financial trouble or difficulty
Example: distressed companies need loans and technical advice; financially hard-pressed Mexican hotels are lowering their prices; we were hard put to meet the mortgage payment; found themselves in a bad way financially
Synonyms: hard-pressed, hard_put, in_a_bad_way, p, facing, or, experiencing, financial, trouble, difficulty, companies, need, loans, and, technical, advice, financially, Mexican, hotels, are, lowering, their, prices, we, were, hard, put, to, meet, the, mortgage, payment, found, themselves, in, a, bad, way
Category: adj.all
